<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="45" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dayton</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 346.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-05-18"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 18, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch No. 303, of the 1st instant,
                            has been received. The department is pleased to notice that you have
                            anticipated the instruction, No. 341, in regard to the transaction of
                            Mr. Adams with Messrs. Howell and Zirman.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">William</hi> L. <hi rend="smallcaps">Dayton</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c</hi>., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>